  "_notes": {
    "generated": "2026-06-26",
    "window": "Last 12 full months 2025-06 through 2026-05; data ~5h lagged, current partial month (2026-06) excluded.",
    "smartContractOps": "stellar.raw.operations, columns ledger_close_time + type. Three Soroban op types present: invoke_host_function (dominant, ~19M-65M/mo), restore_footprint, extend_footprint_ttl. No create_contract/upload_wasm as distinct type values (those are sub-kinds of invoke_host_function host fns).",
    "dex": "stellar.dex.trades, columns ledger_close_time, protocol, usd_amount. 4 protocols: stellar_orderbook, stellar_liquidity_pool, aquarius, soroswap. A small null-protocol bucket in 2026-03 dropped.",
    "stablecoins": "stellar.stablecoins.transfers, columns ledger_close_time, asset_code, usd_amount. Top 10 by 12mo total USD volume. Some assets have null usd in early months (no price); treated as 0.",
    "rwa": "latest market cap = stellar.rwa.balances_eod (block_date=2026-06-26, balance>0) joined to latest stellar.rwa.supply_change.usd_exchange_rate per token_symbol; market_cap = sum(balance)*rate. This is the Stellar-native on-ledger snapshot (209 holders, ~14 tokens). NOTE: balances_eod is Stellar-chain only and undercounts vs. crosschain issued supply (e.g. supply_change cumulative mint for EUTBL/BENJI/USDY is far larger). Monthly 'series' = cumulative running net mint-minus-burn USD (stellar.rwa.supply_change is_mint/is_burn, usd_amount), a directional supply proxy NOT a clean market-cap stock; tokens with null usd_exchange_rate (most WisdomTree, Mercado Bitcoin, Red Swan, Janus Henderson) excluded from priced series. holdersTotal=209 (distinct on-ledger addresses with positive RWA balance today).",
    "blend": "stellar.lending.deposits & stellar.lending.withdrawals (project=protocol='blend'), columns ledger_close_time, usd_amount, token_address. TVL = cumulative monthly (deposits_usd - withdrawals_usd) within the 12mo window, total only. Asset-class breakdown NOT available: token_symbol is null on these rows and token_address holds raw Soroban contract IDs with no symbol map. Cumulative is window-relative (starts at June 2025 net flow, not protocol inception), so absolute level is a lower-bound proxy.",
    "bridges": "stellar.bridges.transfers, columns ledger_close_time, source_chain, destination_chain, direction, usd_amount. inbound = <chain>->stellar, outbound = stellar-><chain>. Values are 12-month TOTALS per chain (single bucket 'total'), NOT a monthly series \u2014 monthly granularity omitted because per-chain monthly volumes are very sparse (most chains <2000 transfers/yr) and would be mostly zeros. Ethereum dominates both directions (~$36M in / $34M out). Chains with null usd (berachain, hyperliquid, flow, xrpl-evm) excluded."
  },
